# 🎤 Speech Emotion Recognition using LSTM

## Overview

This project is a Speech Emotion Recognition system developed as part of the **CodeAlpha AI/ML Internship**.

The system analyzes human speech and predicts the underlying emotion expressed in the audio. It uses **Deep Learning (LSTM)** along with **MFCC (Mel-Frequency Cepstral Coefficients)** features extracted from speech signals.

The final model is integrated with **Streamlit**, allowing users to upload a WAV audio file and receive the predicted emotion.

---

## Problem Statement

Human speech carries emotional information that can be used to understand a person's feelings. This project aims to automatically classify emotions from speech audio using deep learning techniques.

The model predicts emotions such as:

- Happy 😊
- Sad 😢
- Angry 😠
- Calm 😌
- Neutral 😐
- Fearful 😨
- Disgust 🤢
- Surprised 😲

---

## Dataset Used

### RAVDESS Emotional Speech Audio Dataset

This project uses the **Ryerson Audio-Visual Database of Emotional Speech and Song (RAVDESS)** dataset.

Dataset Link:

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/uwrfkaggler/ravdess-emotional-speech-audio

### Dataset Structure

The dataset contains:

- 24 actor folders (`Actor_01` to `Actor_24`)
- Multiple speech recordings for each actor
- Audio samples representing different emotions

